<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>In Winter on Jérémie Litzler</title><link>https://iamjeremie.me/tags/in-winter/</link><description>Recent content in In Winter on Jérémie Litzler</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 22 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://iamjeremie.me/tags/in-winter/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>16 Tips to PREPARE Your Garden for Winter, by Huw Richards</title><link>https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/</link><pubDate>Tue, 22 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/images/2022-11-22-someone-collecting-leaves.jpg" alt="Featured image of post 16 Tips to PREPARE Your Garden for Winter, by Huw Richards" />&lt;p>What can you do to prepare for the winter in your garden? Huw is giving us 16 tips of 30 seconds each.&lt;/p>
&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->
&lt;p>Thanks to Huw Richards for sharing his wisdom and knowledge! I wrote the following notes watching the video published on Huw Richards’s channel. You can watch it using &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qkBT61SGU8k">this YouTube link&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="plant-garlic">Plant garlic&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-1-plant-garlic.jpg"
width="600"
height="308"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-1-plant-garlic_hub3a4da7a1a384e622b78a690f4ef31af_193640_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-1-plant-garlic_hub3a4da7a1a384e622b78a690f4ef31af_193640_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-1-plant-garlic_hub3a4da7a1a384e622b78a690f4ef31af_193640_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Garlic growing in a bed"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Huw always felt that planting garlic before Christmas in his UK climate worked best.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>There are so many ways to enjoy garlic:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>green garlic,&lt;/li>
&lt;li>dried garlic&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="move-plants-into-your-polytunnel">Move plants into your polytunnel&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-2-move-your-plants-to-the-polytunnel.jpg"
width="600"
height="308"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-2-move-your-plants-to-the-polytunnel_hu9dfef8748714e9781e6c474ec0d5b111_156099_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-2-move-your-plants-to-the-polytunnel_hu9dfef8748714e9781e6c474ec0d5b111_156099_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-2-move-your-plants-to-the-polytunnel_hu9dfef8748714e9781e6c474ec0d5b111_156099_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Broccoli flowering"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>If you own one… ;)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It’s a far more favorable environment to grow your winter vegetables.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="clear-your-beds">Clear your beds&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-3-clear-beds.jpg"
width="600"
height="309"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-3-clear-beds_hua1339bcdf57b975d8e9c0c6608ade08a_155180_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-3-clear-beds_hua1339bcdf57b975d8e9c0c6608ade08a_155180_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-3-clear-beds_hua1339bcdf57b975d8e9c0c6608ade08a_155180_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Someone cutting some old plants"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="466px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Leave the roots in the grown.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Try to remove the weeds!&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="pick-up-dead-leaves">Pick up dead leaves&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/images/2022-11-22-someone-collecting-leaves.jpg"
loading="lazy"
alt="Someone racking leaves"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="jli-notice jli-notice-tip" id="Personal note" >
&lt;p class="jli-notice-title">Personal note&lt;/p>&lt;p>I’m currently working on that, for the third year.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I already covered some parts of my garden with a thick and yet light &lt;em>duvet of dead leaves&lt;/em> for the winter.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It serves at least two purposes:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>keep the ground warmer and covered&lt;/li>
&lt;li>help the soil life thrive even in winter&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>This year, I’m planning to gather a lot more than the previous year. At the time of this writing, I have gathered 6 meters cubes already.&lt;/p>&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="collect-grass-clippings">Collect grass clippings&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-5-collect-grass-clippings.jpg"
width="600"
height="309"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-5-collect-grass-clippings_hu8da2ffb2daa1af87ef9f1d88411db3a2_211214_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-5-collect-grass-clippings_hu8da2ffb2daa1af87ef9f1d88411db3a2_211214_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-5-collect-grass-clippings_hu8da2ffb2daa1af87ef9f1d88411db3a2_211214_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Mix of grass clippings and leaves"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="466px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Huw suggests to use the leaves collected before and spread them on your lawn.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Then use your lawn mower to mix the leaves and grass clippings together to obtain a 50/50 mixture great to put on the compost heap.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="plant-field-beans-_vicia-faba_">Plant field beans (&lt;em>Vicia faba&lt;/em>)&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-6-plant-field-beans.jpg"
width="600"
height="307"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-6-plant-field-beans_hu1ab620676df38080b794baf6a81c911d_184631_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-6-plant-field-beans_hu1ab620676df38080b794baf6a81c911d_184631_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-6-plant-field-beans_hu1ab620676df38080b794baf6a81c911d_184631_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="A bed of field beans"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="195"
data-flex-basis="469px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Huw lets them grow during the winter and cut them before they flower in the spring to create a green manure and cover crop.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="conduct-a-tool-and-seeds-audit">Conduct a tool and seeds audit&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-7-conduct-tool-and-seeds-audit.jpg"
width="600"
height="310"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-7-conduct-tool-and-seeds-audit_hu7448f4c86d2c33bb8bafc85f5816dfe2_200303_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-7-conduct-tool-and-seeds-audit_hu7448f4c86d2c33bb8bafc85f5816dfe2_200303_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-7-conduct-tool-and-seeds-audit_hu7448f4c86d2c33bb8bafc85f5816dfe2_200303_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Bags of seeds and labels"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="193"
data-flex-basis="464px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You want to work out what you have left in terms of seeds.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>And check your tools:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Are they working?&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Are they sharp and do they need sharpening?&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>When the Spring time comes, you will be ready to start your planting, seedlings and so forth.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="mulch-your-beds-with-seaweeds">Mulch your beds with seaweeds&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-8-mulch-beds-with-seaweeds.jpg"
width="600"
height="308"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-8-mulch-beds-with-seaweeds_hu23b1cd595a0fd39fd1e90f33930e3ae9_152879_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-8-mulch-beds-with-seaweeds_hu23b1cd595a0fd39fd1e90f33930e3ae9_152879_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-8-mulch-beds-with-seaweeds_hu23b1cd595a0fd39fd1e90f33930e3ae9_152879_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Close up of some seaweed"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Seaweed is full of minerals.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Rain can wash the salt.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="mulch-your-beds-with-compost">Mulch your beds with compost&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-9-mulch-beds-with-compost.jpg"
width="600"
height="308"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-9-mulch-beds-with-compost_huf80f76a52eac410bae11d490f2414657_149762_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-9-mulch-beds-with-compost_huf80f76a52eac410bae11d490f2414657_149762_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-9-mulch-beds-with-compost_huf80f76a52eac410bae11d490f2414657_149762_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Compost applied on a bed"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="continue-planting-if-you-own-a-greenhouse-or-a-polytunnel">Continue planting (if you own a greenhouse or a polytunnel)&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-10-continue-planting.jpg"
width="600"
height="308"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-10-continue-planting_hu1363e151cf8f3b81be7d8fbc3b230367_162786_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-10-continue-planting_hu1363e151cf8f3b81be7d8fbc3b230367_162786_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-10-continue-planting_hu1363e151cf8f3b81be7d8fbc3b230367_162786_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="A thick bed of vegetables"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Continue planting allows us to keep the soil full of life as the plants grow.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Don’t forget to water the indoor beds!&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="green-tomato-chutney">Green tomato Chutney&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-11-use-your-green-tomatoes.jpg"
width="600"
height="306"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-11-use-your-green-tomatoes_hu8daa778dc7b0392589e06f86a2337e31_180006_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-11-use-your-green-tomatoes_hu8daa778dc7b0392589e06f86a2337e31_180006_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-11-use-your-green-tomatoes_hu8daa778dc7b0392589e06f86a2337e31_180006_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Many green tomatoes"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="196"
data-flex-basis="470px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>What is it? See these recipes below that Huw and Sam:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://farmerandchef.co.uk/blog/green-tomato-cider-and-black-garlic-chutney">Green Tomato, Cider and Black Garlic Chutney&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://farmerandchef.co.uk/blog/green-tomato-chutney">Green Tomato Chutney&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="wash-your-polytunnel-and-greenhouse">Wash your polytunnel and greenhouse&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-12-wash-indoor-growing-space.jpg"
width="600"
height="305"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-12-wash-indoor-growing-space_hu63d1937f4f45515c0f6cd4fa2dc1a84d_200177_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-12-wash-indoor-growing-space_hu63d1937f4f45515c0f6cd4fa2dc1a84d_200177_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-12-wash-indoor-growing-space_hu63d1937f4f45515c0f6cd4fa2dc1a84d_200177_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="An aerial view of a garden with beds and a polytunnel"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="196"
data-flex-basis="472px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Why? It will let a lot more light in.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>When? In November.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="propagate-your-plants">Propagate your plants&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-new-plants.jpg"
width="600"
height="307"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-new-plants_hubfc0f1e39755005ed06f6fbed78cf0de_102366_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-new-plants_hubfc0f1e39755005ed06f6fbed78cf0de_102366_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-new-plants_hubfc0f1e39755005ed06f6fbed78cf0de_102366_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="A blackcurrant stem"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="195"
data-flex-basis="469px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;p>When you want to multiply your blackcurrants or other berry bushes,&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Cut the stems that have grown tall at the bottom of the plant&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-cut.jpg"
width="600"
height="309"
srcset="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-cut_hu78b9f05f8996a0cd46bbfe3396f9bcbe_136576_360x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 360w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-cut_hu78b9f05f8996a0cd46bbfe3396f9bcbe_136576_600x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 600w, https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-13-propagate-cut_hu78b9f05f8996a0cd46bbfe3396f9bcbe_136576_1024x0_resize_q75_box.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="A stem being cut"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="466px"
>
&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Plant them in a dedicated bed.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>During winter, they will root and you will be able to transplant them where you want in the spring.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can also do this in a pot to sell. This can be a source of money to buy seeds.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="jli-notice jli-notice-tip" id="Personal note" >
&lt;p class="jli-notice-title">Personal note&lt;/p>&lt;p>I will do that with my gooseberry bush that has grown big and I want to get more of them next year.&lt;/p>&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="do-something-with-the-container-full-of-compost">Do something with the container full of compost&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>If you grow anything in containers, you can toss the used compost back into the compost heap and mix it well with the rest.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="conduct-an-infrastructure-audit">Conduct an infrastructure audit&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/tips-to-prepare-your-garden-for-winter-huw-richards/images/tip-15-audit-your-infrastructure.jpg"
width="600"
height="307"
